articles.description: Jalen Hudson scored 27 points and Florida throttled Alabama's offense in a 73-52 victory on Tuesday night.
articles.headline: Hudson scores 27, Florida throttles Alabama 73-52

images.caption: Jalen Hudson drives and tells Donta Hall to smile after putting him on a poster.
images.name: Hudson throws down emphatic slam on Alabama

articles.description: Jahad Thomas drained 15 field goals to score a career-high 40 points and lead UMass Lowell to its third straight win, 92-77 over New Hampshire on Tuesday night to conclude the regular-season schedule.
articles.headline: Thomas has 40 points, UMass Lowell runs past New Hampshire

articles.description: Tennessee head coach Rick Barnes talks about his team's offensive display and limited turnovers against Mississippi State.
articles.headline: Barnes proud of Vols' offense vs. Bulldogs

images.caption: Tennessee head coach Rick Barnes talks about his team's offensive display and limited turnovers against Mississippi State.
images.name: Barnes proud of Vols' offense vs. Bulldogs

articles.description: James Demery scored 21 points, Taylor Funk had 17 and Saint Joseph's stunned Atlantic 10 champion and No. 17 Rhode Island 78-48 on Tuesday night.
articles.headline: Saint Joseph's stuns No. 17 URI 78-48

images.caption: James Demery throws down a big dunk in transition for St. Joseph's.
images.name: Demery hammers it down with one hand

articles.description: Jeffrey Carroll scored 21 points, Cameron McGriff had 19 and Oklahoma State cruised past Iowa State 80-71 on Tuesday, sweeping the season series with the Cyclones.
articles.headline: Oklahoma State cruises past Iowa State 80-71

articles.description: Ty Jones scored 17 points on 8-of-9 shooting and Charleston Southern opened the Big South Tournament with a 68-51 victory over Presbyterian on Tuesday night.
articles.headline: Charleston Southern beats Presbyterian in Big South tourney
